{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M2SetupResponse generation in M3AP MCE handler\n\n### Summary\nThe `m2ap_MCE_generate_m2_setup_response` function in the M3AP implementation was not generating complete M2SetupResponse messages due to commented-out code sections. This caused the MCE to send malformed responses during M2 setup procedures, leading to connection failures with peer nodes.\n\nThe issue was traced to `/repo/openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_generate_messages.c` where all the mandatory Information Elements (IEs) for the M2SetupResponse were commented out. When called, the function would only generate an empty PDU without the required GlobalMCE_ID, ServedCells, and GUGroupIDList IEs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_generate_messages.c`: Uncommented and properly implemented all mandatory IEs in `m2ap_MCE_generate_m2_setup_response`\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE_generate_messages.h`: Fixed function signature and header file consistency\n- Removed the typo file `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE_generate_messsages.c` that contained a commented-out version\n- Fixed include references in `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_generate_messages.c` to point to correct header\n- Corrected naming inconsistencies in `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_generate_messages.h`\n\n"
}